#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
veropkg - Veronic Linux Package Manager
Version 0.2.2

Improvements over v0.1:
  - Input validation on all package names (path traversal / injection blocked)
  - SSL-verified downloads with TLS 1.2 minimum
  - Non-blocking lock with clear error when already locked
  - require_root() now enforced on mutating commands
  - safe_extract() adds file-size cap and realpath-based traversal check
  - staging temp dir always cleaned up (try/finally)
  - Circular dependency error now shows the full cycle path
  - autoremove command implemented
  - info command (package details)
  - list --verbose shows timestamps
  - search shows [installed] marker
  - SandboxEngine adds --unshare-net and --die-with-parent
  - Read chunk size raised to 64 KB for throughput
  - Added structured logging (-v / --verbose)
  - --version flag added
  - [v0.2.1] upgrade command fully implemented with file cleanup and dependency resolution
  - [v0.2.2] Advanced Exception hierarchy (NetworkError, LockError, ChecksumError) with hints
"""

